This paper deals with congestion control and scheduling in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI). The paper also incorporates quality of service (QoS) requirements, which is a topic related to information theory (IT). The paper proposes a joint congestion control and scheduling algorithm, which is a topic related to systems and control (SY). The paper also mentions the use of stochastic network theory, which is a topic related to multimedia (MM). Finally, the paper deals with resource allocation, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC).
